ertarianism is that its primary goal is the elimination of' b'government coercion except in a very limited cases.' b'' b'but what good is change if there is no tracable improvement in the human' b"condition? who would ever support the change if you tell them it won't" b'improve their lives? i know that there are, and will be, libertarians' b'who will jump in now and say that it will improve our lives. i can deal' b"with that. all i'm saying is that improving the human condition must" b'be the primary goal of any organization.' b'' b'ian sutherland' b'' b'------------------------------------------------------------------------------' b'"who said anything about panicking?" snapped authur. garrett johnson' b'settled into the situation and found my bearings.' b'then i\'ll start panicking!" douglas adams' b'------------------------------------------------------------------------------' 